description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 1600 channel (as well as AIA 1700) often shows a web-like pattern of
bright areas that highlight places where bundles of magnetic fields lines are
concentrated. However, small areas with a lot of field lines will appear
black, usually near sunspots and active regions.

**Where:** Transition region and upper photosphere

**Wavelength:** 1600 angstroms (0.00000016 m) = Far Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** thrice ionized carbon (C IV) and Continuum

**Characteristic temperatures:** 6,000 K (11,000 F), and 100,000 K (180,000 F)

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0335 channel (as well as AIA 211) highlights the active region of the
outer atmosphere of the Sun - the corona. Active regions, solar flares, and
coronal mass ejections will appear bright here. The dark areas - or coronal
holes - are places where very little radiation is emitted, yet are the main
source of solar wind particles.

**Where:** Active regions of the corona

**Wavelength:** 335 angstroms (0.0000000335 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** 15 times ionized iron (Fe XVI)

**Characteristic temperature:** 2.8 million K (5 million F)

description: ['second Moon landing and sixth crewed flight of the United States Apollo program']
parsed caption:
Apollo 12 Hasselblad image from film magazine 49/Z - EVA-2  
This is figure 1-30 of the _Apollo 12 Preliminary Science Report_ , which has
the following caption:  

    The core-sample tool embedded in the lunar surface near Halo Crater. In this southeast-looking view, the loosely compacted lunar soil is clearly visible, and Halo Crater can be seen in the background.

(This is an error - the core tube was collected south of Halo crater and this
photo is looking southeast, so Halo can't be in the photo.)  
This photo is also shown as figure 10-67 and has the following caption:  

    Double-core tube at the completion of driving. No disturbance of the surrounding surface is evident as a result of driving the core tube.

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0094 channel (as well as AIA 131) is designed to study solar flares. It
measures extremely hot temperatures around 6 million Kelvin (10.8 million F).
It can take images every 2 seconds (instead of 10) in a reduced field of view
in order to look at flares in more detail.

**Where:** Flaring regions of the corona

**Wavelength:** 94 angstroms (0.0000000094 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet/soft
X-rays

**Primary ions seen:** 17 times ionized iron (Fe XVIII)

**Characteristic temperature:** 6 million K (10.8 million F)

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0193 channel highlights the outer atmosphere of the Sun - called the
corona - as well as hot flare plasma. Hot active regions, solar flares, and
coronal mass ejections will appear bright here. The dark areas - called
coronal holes - are places where very little radiation is emitted, yet are the
main source of solar wind particles.

**Where:** Corona and hot flare plasma

**Wavelength:** 193 angstroms (0.0000000193 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** 11 times ionized iron (Fe XII)

**Characteristic temperature:** 1.25 million K (2.25 million F)

[Austria](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Austria "en:Austria")).

description: ['1962 border conflict between China and India', 'border dispute between China and India', 'disputed territory administered by China', 'Mountain pass in India', 'plain in India', 'river in disputed Aksai Chin region', 'river in China and India', 'soda lake in the Himalayas', 'village in Ladakh, India', 'Disputed border area between India and China', 'river in India and Pakistan', 'river in Asia']
parsed caption:
The map depicts the 1956 and 1960 claim lines of China in Ladakh, as well as
lines of actual control before and after the 1962 [Sino-Indian
War](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/en:Sino-Indian_War "w:en:Sino-Indian War").
Chinese proposal that both sides should withdraw 20 km from the ceasefire line
is also illustrated.

Legend:

  * Green line – 1956 claim line of China
  * Dark grey line – 1960 claim line of China (often coincides with the Orange line)
  * Blue line - Chinese advance in 1959
  * Purple line - Chinese position before the 1962 war ("Line of separation")
  * Orange line - Chinese position at the end of the 1962 war ("Ceasefire line")
  * Dotted orange lines - 20 km separation from the ceasefire line (Chinese proposal for truce)

**FY-kus** or **FIK-us** from the Latin for Fig **ar-not-ee-AH-nuh** \-- named
for George Arnold Walker-Arnott, Scottish botanist

description: ['sports club based around boats', 'structure, typically with a roof and walls, standing more or less permanently in one place', "any significant accumulation of water, generally on a planet's surface", 'perennial woody plant', 'freestanding structure preventing movement across a boundary', 'opening to admit light or air', 'flat, movable structure used to open and close an entrance', 'rock or artificial rock-like material']
parsed caption:
[Holma Boat Club](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Holma,_Lysekil_Municipality
"en:Holma, Lysekil Municipality") at
[Gullmarn](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gullmarn "en:Gullmarn") fjord,
Lysekil Municipality, Sweden. This part of the fjord consists mostly of nature
reserves, so there are no street lights and very few houses in the area. The
scene was only lit by the moon, at the time approaching full at 97.2%. The
shot was made in a north-easterly direction, so the brighter sky on the right
side is not the setting sun but the [E6
highway](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_route_E6 "en:European route
E6"), the Gothenburg - Oslo stretch. To reduce noise, most of the photo was
done by merging three exposures using _[this
technique](//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Stacking_to_reduce_noise.jpg
"File:Stacking to reduce noise.jpg")_. This noise reduction can't be use on
the sky since the stars move (relatively speaking), so it was only done to the
non-sky part of the photo.

parsed caption:
66150 WBAT ABERTHWPS 784C46CH09 0 TOWER COL N 5D A

DB Schenker Rail (UK) Ltd's class 66 (JT42CWR) number 66150 in English, Welsh
and Scottish Railway maroon livery with zigzag gold band, large number and EWS
logo. Here it is photographed entering Pontypridd Railway station heading
northwards working 6C46 on 9 April 2015. The exEWS empty bogie coal hopper
wagons being hauled from Aberthaw Power Station to Tower Colliery were to be
loaded with anthracite (a variety of hard coal that has a high carbon content
with few impurities so releases a large amount of energy per weight) excavated
from the Tower Colliery open cast mine. 66150 (works number 968702-150) was
built by General Motors Electro-Motive Division, London, Ontario, Canada in
1998 and unloaded from the Heavy Lift Ship MV "Gajah Borneo" at Newport Docks
on 18 August 1999.

description: ['Khmer traditional music genre and also an ensemble performing it']
parsed caption:
Postcard 1662 by Pierre Dieulefils (mailed in Hanoi, 1907) depicting a
Cambodian orchestra, labeled "Orchestre pour les dances royales" (Orchestra
for royal dances), at Phnom Penh, Cambodia. Dieulefils was a French
photographer who lived in Hanoi and took pictures in both Vietnam and
Cambodia, and published his images in Hanoi as postcards. Instruments from the
left: front row: [samphor](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/samphor "w:samphor")
drum, [roneat dek](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/roneat_dek "w:roneat dek")
([metalophone](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/metalophone "w:metalophone")),
[roneat ek](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/roneat_ek "w:roneat ek") (bamboo
xylophone), [roneat thung](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/roneat_thung
"w:roneat thung") (bamboo xylophone),
[sralai](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/sralai "w:sralai") reed pipe, [skor
thom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/skor_thom "w:skor thom") drums, other
drums. Back row from the left: sralai, [kong von
thom](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/kong_von_thom "w:kong von thom"), [kong
von toch](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/kong_von_toch "w:kong von toch").

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0094 channel (as well as AIA 131) is designed to study solar flares. It
measures extremely hot temperatures around 6 million Kelvin (10.8 million F).
It can take images every 2 seconds (instead of 10) in a reduced field of view
in order to look at flares in more detail.

**Where:** Flaring regions of the corona

**Wavelength:** 94 angstroms (0.0000000094 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet/soft
X-rays

**Primary ions seen:** 17 times ionized iron (Fe XVIII)

**Characteristic temperature:** 6 million K (10.8 million F)

parsed caption:
Biografen Saga, ett av Höganäs finaste smultronställen. Lokalen byggdes 1883
och användes först som teatersalong. Sexton år senare, 6 januari 1899, visades
den första filmen.

Glöm inte att besöka Saga nästa gång ni passerar Höganäs. Glid in i
biomörkret, snacka film med ”Bosse Bio”, köp popcorn och njut av både film och
biosalong.

bright areas that highlight places where bundles of magnetic fields lines are
concentrated. However, small areas with a lot of field lines will appear
black, usually near sunspots and active regions.

**Where:** Temperature minimum and photosphere

**Wavelength:** 1700 angstroms (0.00000017 m) = Far Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** Continuum

**Characteristic temperature:** 6,000 K (11,000 F)

description: ['Vice-Commandant of the United States Coast Guard']
parsed caption:
Lt. Christopher Stoeckler, an MH-60 pilot with Air Station Kodiak, expalins
the course of events during the rescue of victims from the recent plane crash
case that claimed the life of former Alaska senator Ted Stevens to Coast Guard
Vice Adm. Sally Brice-O'Hara, Coast Guard vice commandant, and Alice Hill,
senior counselor to the secretary of Homeland Security, during a visit to the
Air Station Sept. 3, 2010. The dignitaries visit to Kodiak was an effort to
better understand the scope of Alaska operations and the inherint challenges
of operating in the remote region.

parsed caption:
Nach dem Unfall in der Nacht vom 12. zum 13. September, Richtung Geithain. Das
Nordende des Überbaues ist aus den Lagern gerissen und in Blickrichtung nach
rechts verschoben worden. Der Sattelzug mit einem Bagger auf dem Auflieger kam
aus Richtung Großpösna (von links, Eisenbahnstrecke und Straße kreuzen in
spitzem Winkel) und fuhr stadteinwärts. Der Schaden scheint auf den ersten
Blick von oben beherrschbar zu sein, doch ist der Überbau material- und
altersbedingt unreparierbar beschädigt.  
Die Brücke ist nach dem Unfall in der Nacht wohl irrtümlich noch einmal
befahren worden, zum Aufnahmezeitpunkt gegen 8.00 morgens war die Strecke
jedoch schon gesperrt.

under the banner of "Ireland For All". The Dublin rally was organised by the
newly founded organisation, "Le Chéile", which comprises almost 50 member
organisations and which had called for a march in support of "diversity not
division", and opposition to racism.

PLEASE, NO invitations or self promotions, THEY WILL BE DELETED. My photos are

The Warsaw Uprising of 1944 ended tragically. The monument is in two parts;
one part showing the insurgents defending a barricade and the second showing
soldiers and others escaping down a manhole into the sewers, a reference to
the 2,000 fighters who disappeared down a single manhole on September 2nd
1944.

The Warsaw Uprising against the Nazi occupiers is one of Poland's most famous
battles. Over 225,000 civilians (as well as 20,000 soldiers) lost their lives
in a battle that lasted for 63 days.

file_name: File:230315-F-ZB805-0554 - Shaw AFB assists U.S. Marines during RF-N 23-2.jpg
description: ['United States Marine Corps aviation unit', 'military rank', 'military exercise']
parsed caption:
U.S. Marine Corps Sgt. David Kearney, Marine Corps Air Station Miramar, San
Diego, structural hydraulic mechanic, oversees the work of U.S. Air Force 20th
Maintenance Group (MXG) aircraft structural maintenance Airmen during exercise
Red Flag-Nellis (RF-N) 23-2 at Nellis Air Force Base, Nevada, March 15, 2023.
The 20th MXG supports each of the coalition forces and allies during RF-N 23-2
when maintenance outside of their capabilities is required, ensuring all
forces can stay ready during the high-intensity training exercise. (U.S. Air
Force photo by Staff Sgt. Madeline Herzog)

description: ['Austrian and American actor, bodybuilder, and politician (born 1947)']
parsed caption:
O Governador do Estado de São Paulo João Doria, recebeu o ator e ex-governador
da Califórnia, Arnold Schwarzenegger, para discutir ações de sustentabilidade
e economia verde.

Schwarzenegger é o idealizador da R20 - Regions of Climate Action, uma
organização ambientalista sem fins lucrativos, fundada em setembro de 2011. Em
São Paulo, está destinada ao desenvolvimento de projetos sustentáveis e apoia
o Programa Município Verde Azul, da Secretaria de Estado de Infraestrutura e
Meio Ambiente. Local: São Paulo/SP Data: 14/04/2019 Foto: Governo do Estado de
São Paulo

description: ['American football player, running back, return specialist']
parsed caption:
Ottoville, AS, November 30, 2009 -- The Federal Coordinating Officer for the
Federal Emergency Management Agency in American Samoa, Kenneth Tingman, and
Evelyn Langford, American Samoa Governors Authorized Representative, discuss
the recovery status with former Chicago Bears football player, Gabe Reid
(white t-shirt) and former Philadelphia Eagles football player, Reno Mahe
(gray t-shirt). Reid and Mahe recently visited the island to observe the
tsunami damage and to thank the workers assisting with disaster recovery. From
left to right: Gabe Reid, Reno Mahe, Evelyn Langford, Kenneth Tingman.

parsed caption:
The City of Rockhampton, an [Electric Tilt
Train](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electric_Tilt_Train "en:Electric Tilt
Train"), is one of two identical high-speed [tilting
trains](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/tilting_train "en:tilting train")
operated by [Queensland Rail](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Queensland_Rail
"en:Queensland Rail") on the [North Coast
line](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Coast_railway_line,_Queensland
"en:North Coast railway line, Queensland") from
[Brisbane](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roma_Street_railway_station "en:Roma
Street railway station") to
[Bundaberg](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bundaberg_railway_station
"en:Bundaberg railway station") and
[Rockhampton](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rockhampton_railway_station
"en:Rockhampton railway station") which entered service in November 1998.

description: ['star at the centre of the Solar System']
parsed caption:
AIA 0131 channel (as well as AIA 094) is designed to study solar flares. It
measures extremely hot temperatures around 10 million K (18 million F), as
well as cool plasmas around 400,000 K (720,000 F). It can take images every 2
seconds (instead of 10) in a reduced field of view in order to look at flares
in more detail.  
  
**Where:** Flaring regions of the corona

**Wavelength:** 131 angstroms (0.0000000131 m) = Extreme Ultraviolet

**Primary ions seen:** 20 and 7 times ionized iron (Fe VIII, Fe XXI)

**Characteristic temperatures:** 10 million K (18 million F)

  *[![](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/53/Info_non-talk.svg/15px-Info_non-talk.svg.png)]: Files from the inventories “Bild 101 Propagandakompanien der Wehrmacht” and “Bild 183 ADN” may have particularly biased or politically extreme descriptions.
